.ds n) explain_ptrace_or_die
.cp 0  \" Solaris defaults to ''.cp 1'', sheesh.
.TH explain_ptrace_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_ptrace_or_die \- process trace and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_ptrace_or_die(3)" \
    "process trace and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/ptrace.h>
.sp 0.3
long explain_ptrace_or_die(int request, pid_t pid, void *addr, void *data);
.br
long explain_ptrace_on_error(int request, pid_t pid, void *addr, void
*data);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]explain_ptrace_or_die\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]ptrace\fP(2) system call. On failure an explanation will be printed to
\f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from the \f[I]explain_ptrace\fP(3) function, and
then the process terminates by calling \f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.PP
The \f[B]explain_ptrace_on_error\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]ptrace\fP(2) system call. On failure an explanation will be printed to
\f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from the \f[I]explain_ptrace\fP(3) function, but
still returns to the caller.
.TP 8n
\f[I]request\fP
The request, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]ptrace\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]pid\fP
The pid, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]ptrace\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]addr\fP
The addr, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]ptrace\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]data\fP
The data, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]ptrace\fP(2) system call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH RETURN VALUE
The \f[B]explain_ptrace_or_die\fP function only returns on success, see
\f[I]ptrace\fP(2) for more information. On failure, prints an explanation
and exits, it does not return.
.PP
The \f[B]explain_ptrace_on_error\fP function always returns the value
return by the wrapped \f[I]ptrace\fP(2) system call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH EXAMPLE
The \f[B]explain_ptrace_or_die\fP function is intended to be used in a
fashion similar to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.nf
long result = explain_ptrace_or_die(request, pid, addr, data);
.fi
.ft R
.RE
